Reading those "my dad with dementia forgot who my mom is, but cries when he sees her photo" stories did not make me any more spiritual as a child, but they really did help crystalize just how much I truly despised the concept of disease, the profound hatred I felt for it

Any warmth in such stories comes from the displayed love, but the disease serves to cover the love, not to "reveal" it

Dr. Ray Peat formulated this as "We need to understand that the human condition is problematic"
